article.headline: Green Bay 75, Youngstown St. 67
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Rahmon Fletcher scored 28 points in 28 minutes Saturday to lead Wisconsin-Green Bay past Youngstown State, 75-67. Bryquis Perine scored 15 points for the Phoenix (10-3, 3-0 Horizon), and Randy Berry had 14 points and 11 rebounds. Fletcher made four of his six 3-point attempts and was 10-for-13 from the free-throw line. Vytas Sulskis scored 17 to lead the Penguins (4-6, 0-3). Zack Rebillot had 10 off the bench. Youngstown State's reserves outscored Wisconsin-Green Bay's 28-9, and the Penguins held a 30-18 edge in points in the paint, but it wasn't enough. The Phoenix's eight-point lead at the end was the largest lead of the game. Youngstown State led 32-29 at halftime.
